Table 4. To investigate models with the same size, but one 
pre-trained on a larger dataset, we compare the results of ResNet-50 and ResNeXt-50 32x4d. On 
average across all five datasets, the gain of SMA over ERM (our runs) is 2.5% for ResNet-50 and 
3.9% for ResNeXt-50 32x4d. The gain of EoA over ERM is larger: 4% vs 5% respectively. This 
suggests that pre-training the model on a larger dataset increases the gain of model averaging and 
EoA over the corresponding ERM baseline, while the ERM performance itself improves.
